# Fitness & Wellness App Database (MySQL)

This is a MySQL-based relational database project for a fitness and wellness tracking app. The system was designed as a group class project to support features like user registration, trainer management, workout tracking, diet plans, and subscription processing.

## 👨‍👩‍👧‍👦 Team Members
- Nordine Djema *(Lead database developer & schema designer)*
- Abdul
- Yannis
- Amina
- Emmanuel

## 📋 Features Modeled
- User profile registration & unique email enforcement
- Workout & diet plan assignment by certified trainers
- Body metrics and fitness progress logging
- Subscription tiers with payment tracking
- Secure database constraints and entity relationships

## 🗂️ Files Included
- `create_tables.sql` — All CREATE TABLE statements with constraints
- `insert_sample_data.sql` — Sample data (users, workouts, plans, etc.)
- `query_examples.sql` — Sample queries using JOINs, filters, etc.
- `ER_Diagram.png` — Entity-Relationship diagram
- `relational_schema.png` — Relational schema design

## 📌 Technologies Used
- MySQL
- SQL (DDL & DML)
- Draw.io (for ERD)

## 🚀 Project Goals
This project simulates a real-world backend database for a fitness platform. It includes multiple user roles, business logic, and data integrity enforcement to help users track their fitness goals securely and efficiently.
